race.comment: O'INVINCIBLE (2) talented mare who resumes after being plagued by wet tracks over the winter months. Looks ready to go after the two trials and Chambers' 3kg claim will see her take catching. LULL (10) resumed with the one trial when a battling sixth over 1000m at Kembla Grange. Lone victory came second-up and has the upside to play a leading role from the good draw. DIVO (3) failed to back up his good second here two-back, when a fading seventh to The Three Hundred over 1200m in the Wyong Magic Millions 3&4yo Classic. Winning apprentice hops back aboard and shapes as an each-way prospect. VANLEE (9) resuming. Came to the end of her prep fourth-up when a plugging seventh over 1100m at Hawkesbury. Fitted with the two trials and can take a hand in the finish.
